#11206
Knight's Mansion~
Upon the eastern wall is the extension of the fireplace directly below this
room, from the floor up to the ceiling.  You look about at a few miscellaneous
paintings hung upon the walls in this room.  The revelations of the brilliance
in this art work is the sort of thing you might see on a screen in an Indian
restaurant in Panama.  With the tapestries of mustached riders with scimitars.
The ivory balls, one inside the other, their seams showing.  The long tea room,
mirrors on both sides, and the tired looking rubber plants.  One depicts a
scene of a boat in what looks to be a dark swamp, oared across the river that
is death by a reaper.  A very grim picture...
~
